    <div class="comment searchable">
      <p>
As for how to customize the CSRF error page, <a class="ext-link" href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/csrf/#rejected-requests"><span class="icon">​</span>see the docs</a>.<br />
</p>
<p>
I'll accept this ticket to add an FAQ to the list started in <a class="closed ticket" href="/ticket/26165" title="Cleanup/optimization: Add an FAQ that explains why Django's CSRF isn't vulnerable (closed: fixed)">#26165</a>. In his security talk at <a class="ext-link" href="https://opbeat.com/events/duth/"><span class="icon">​</span>Django Under the Hood 2015</a>, Florian said rotating the token on login "is a security feature and won't change."<br />
</p>

    </div>

