    <div class="comment searchable">
      <p>
Hi thanks Aymeric and Tim for your quick response and reference! <br />
</p>
<p>
My additional proposal would be to change the wording of the error message to something an end-user would understand, for example:<br />
</p>
<p>
Access forbidden (403 error)<br />
</p>
<p>
Please reload the page to try again.<br />
 <br />
Your request was aborted due to a CSRF verification failure.<br />
</p>
<p>
Please report to the site's administrator if the problem persists.<br />
</p>

